title: For Sale:  Beretta Nano 9mm - Single Stack Handgun with Extra Mag, Holster, Lock, and Box
postcontent:
I'm selling a Beretta Nano because I no longer carry it. This thing is an excellent self defense or carry gun. The gun is in *perfect* mechanical shape - I baby all my guns and this one was no exception. I shot just a few hundred rounds through it (less than 500) and it's been cleaned and lubricated with FrogLube. It has never failed or hiccupped or malfunctioned. The only thing that isn't perfect is that it shows a bit of wear on the finish towards the muzzle due to a holster I've since gotten rid of.
It comes with the two factory magazines (one 6round flush mag, one pinky grip 8round) and an additional factory magazine I purchased (6round flush).
I've applied rubberized Talon grips to it, which are wonderful and make the gun much more pleasant and grippy in the hands. If you want to go back to the factory smooth plastic finish, you can just peel them off and apply a little rubbing alcohol to remove the adhesive completely. 
It comes with a Blackpoint Tactical IWB holster, which go for around ~80 retail.
It also comes with the factory box and factory security lock.
It also comes with a spare firing pin assembly. You likely won't need it, I only bought it in order to reach the "free shipping" threshold on an online order, but hey, if anything in your firing pin assembly breaks, you'll be set.
I will only sell to folks who have a valid Georgia Weapons License. No exceptions.
I can meet you at any reputable public place in the Atlanta area. I respond quickly to messages, usually within 30 minutes. Feel free to contact me with offers or questions. Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 36 9MM Shotgun
postcontent: You are buying 1 WINCHESTER MODEL 36, 9MM RIMFIRE SHOTGUN. This shotgun was produced between 1920 and 1927. Only 20,306 were produced. It has an 18” barrel and will shoot either long shot, short shot, or ball. As can be seen the trigger guard is very unique. It weighs a little less than 3 pounds. These guns did not have serial numbers. On the barrel of the gun is the following” Manufactured by Winchester Repeating Arms, New Haven, Conn, USA, Aug 29, 1899, Model 36 Shotgun, Cal. 9MM Rim Fire, Winchester Trade Mark Reg. US Pat. Office & FGN”. There is an oval with the letters P over a W that is just forward of the receiver and also on the front of the bolt. I have had this gun for about 3 years and have never fired it. I have lightly swabbed the inside and outside of the barrel and rubbed the stock with a very light coat of oil. The shells are still available thru Froichi.  I had the gun informally appraised by a gun buyer in my area for the purpose of trading. He stated that the condition is in the 80% range. Based upon his appraisal it is all original including the unbroken and uncracked butt plate. There is some minor pitting at the very end of the barrel and it has most of the original bluing. The barrel is in good condition with some minor pitting. Mechanically the gun functions as expected. All original hardware.
